<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Create a Literary and Arts Magazine</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="3" relname="attribution">Ever thought</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1002" relname="span">about creating a literary and arts magazine for your high school or college ?</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1003" relname="joint">Even just for fun ?</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="condition">If so ,</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="span">this step by step process</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="purpose">for creating a literary and arts magazine will be very useful to you .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1008" relname="sequence">Getting Started</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="span">Create a website or portal for works</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="10" relname="purpose">to be submitted .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="span">Decide on content</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">( poems , short stories , art etc ) .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="span">This may include hiring an IT person</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="purpose">to help set up the site .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="span">The IT person should include procedures for authors and artists to submit their works ,</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="elaboration">along with username accounts for each member of the review team .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1011" relname="joint">A reviewing and scoring system should also be created .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1019" relname="span">Get a group of people together</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="19" relname="purpose">to help create the magazine .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1011" relname="joint">This may be in the form of a club or actual class .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1011" relname="joint">Make sure to assign important positions to members of the Magazine team such as Editor in Chief , Assistant Editor , etc.</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1023" relname="sequence">Once a team is assembled ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1023" relname="sequence">start promotion !</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="span">Design flyers/posters</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="purpose">to put up around your community or school campus .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1011" relname="joint">Also think about creating various social media accounts for the magazine such as Facebook , Instagram , and Twitter .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="span">This will get the word out to possible authors and artists</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">who are interested in submitting their work .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1011" relname="joint">Do n't forget to include a deadline for submissions and a link to the magazine 's website on the flyers and social media accounts !</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1011" relname="joint">That way potential authors and artists will know exactly where to submit their work .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1011" relname="joint">Reviewing Content</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1011" relname="joint">Once works are in ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1011" relname="joint">start reviewing !</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="span">Make sure to give you and your team a couple weeks</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="purpose">to do this .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">Review each piece thoroughly</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="purpose">so that it is given proper consideration .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="span">Meet frequently with your club or class</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="purpose">to discuss works with the highest scores .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="span">These will probably be the ones</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="elaboration">chosen for publication !</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1036" relname="joint">While reviewing works ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="span">get in touch with a graphic designer</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="44" relname="elaboration">who can create the cover and template for the magazine .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1046" relname="span">He or she is essential</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="elaboration">in bringing your vision for the magazine to life !</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="span">Also get an idea of the cost for printing and how many copies need to be made .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">An experienced printing company will be needed for this .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="preparation">Make final decisions !</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="span">Choose the works</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="51" relname="elaboration">that will be published in the magazine .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1050" relname="joint">Notify the authors and artists</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1053" relname="sequence">and possibly request brief personal biographies to be included in the magazine .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1054" relname="joint">Have the editing team look over the chosen works for any grammatical errors .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="span">Works should be proofread multiple times by each editor</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="purpose">to ensure little to no mistakes .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1057" relname="elaboration">The Final Stages</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="span">Send out final drafts of the short stories and poems , author bios , and editor 's note to the graphic designer .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="59" relname="elaboration">He or she will place these into the finished magazine template .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1054" relname="joint">Send to print !</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1054" relname="joint">Allow 1-2 weeks for the magazine to be printed prior to publication .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1054" relname="joint">Celebrate !</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1063" relname="contrast">This step is optional ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1063" relname="contrast">but a nice party for the magazine team , authors , and artists is always a plus !</segment>
